{"metadata":{"symbolKind":"class","roleHeading":"Class","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"StaticMutex","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutex"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"StaticMutex"}],"externalID":"s:4GLib11StaticMutexC","role":"symbol"},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol"],"kind":"relationships","title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StaticMutex","kind":"identifier"}],"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Prior to GLib 2.32, GStaticMutex had the significant advantage"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"that it doesn’t need to be created at run-time, but can be defined","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"at compile-time. Since 2.32, "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" can be statically allocated"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"as well, and GStaticMutex has been deprecated."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Here is a version of our "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"give_me_next_number()"},{"type":"text","text":" example using"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"a GStaticMutex:"}]},{"syntax":null,"code":["  int","  give_me_next_number (void)","  {","    static int current_number = 0;","    int ret_val;","    static GStaticMutex mutex = G_STATIC_MUTEX_INIT;","","    g_static_mutex_lock (&mutex);","    ret_val = current_number = calc_next_number (current_number);","    g_static_mutex_unlock (&mutex);","","    return ret_val;","  }"],"type":"codeListing"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Sometimes you would like to dynamically create a mutex. If you don’t","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"want to require prior calling to ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", because your code","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"should also be usable in non-threaded programs, you are not able to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"use ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_mutex_new()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and thus ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Mutex"},{"text":", as that requires a prior call to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_thread_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". In these cases you can also use a ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":".","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It must be initialized with ","type":"text"},{"code":"g_static_mutex_init()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" before using it"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"and freed with with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_free()"},{"text":" when not needed anymore to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"free up any allocated resources.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Even though ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"text":" is not opaque, it should only be used with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the following functions, as it is defined differently on different","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"platforms."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions apart from"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"g_static_mutex_get_mutex()","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" can also be used even if ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_thread_init()"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"has not yet been called. Then they do nothing, apart from","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_static_mutex_trylock()"},{"type":"text","text":" which does nothing but returning "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"All of the g_static_mutex_* functions are actually macros. Apart from","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"taking their addresses, you can however use them as if they were"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"functions.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","isActive":true},{"text":" type acts as an owner of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"code":"GStaticMutex","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"It provides the methods that can operate on this data type through "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexProtocol","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" conformance."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutex","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" as a strong reference or owner of a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStaticMutex"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Use "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StaticMutexRef","t